title.narrative: 103 PLANNING, MONITORING, EVALUATION, EVIDENCE GENERATION & KNOWLEDGE MANAGEMENT,

description.narrative: By 2022, government and partners at national, state and district level have access to disaggregated data and evidence, with the capacity to use it for prioritizing policy, planning, monitoring and budgetary actions to scale up essential RMNCH+A interventions including demand generation, with focus on marginalized groups, especially the girl child., which contributes to Child Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Business and Key Business Stakeholders demonstrate growing willingness, commitment and resource allocation for protecting and promoting child rights in policy and practice by 2022
